German

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Middle High German valke, from Old High German falco, from Proto-West Germanic *falkō, from Proto-Germanic *falkô.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ˈfalkə/
  • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)
  • Hyphenation: Fal‧ke

Noun

[edit]

Falke m (weak, genitive Falken, plural Falken, diminutive Fälkchen n or Fälklein n, feminine Fälkin)

  1. (birds) falcon
  2. (politics) hawk, hard-liner

Declension

[edit]
Declension of Falke [masculine, weak]
singular plural
indef. def. noun def. noun
nominative ein der Falke die Falken
genitive eines des Falken der Falken
dative einem dem Falken den Falken
accusative einen den Falken die Falken
